    "character/races/humans/gillikinese": {
      "title": "Gillikinese",
      "content": "<h1>Gillikinese</h1>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>\"The Gillikinese have always believed themselves the natural aristocracy of Oz—educated, refined, and conveniently forgetful of how that refinement was purchased.\"</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h2>Overview</h2>\n\n<p>The Gillikinese are the human inhabitants of Gillikin, the northern province of Oz. Distinguished by their purple-hued fashion and their long-standing emphasis on education and refinement, they represent the intellectual and aristocratic elite of Oz. Shiz University, located in Gillikin, has been the premier institution of learning in Oz for centuries, and Gillikinese culture revolves around academic achievement, social status, and the preservation of tradition.</p>\n\n<p>However, beneath this polished exterior lies a complex history. The Gillikinese aristocracy built their wealth and status through the exploitation of Animals and the lower classes, though many prefer to focus on their cultural contributions rather than examine the foundations of their privilege. The region's history with Animal rights activism, particularly surrounding Shiz University, has created deep divisions within Gillikinese society.</p>\n\n<p>Modern Gillikinese find themselves torn between tradition and change. Some cling to the old ways, while others question the systems that gave their ancestors power. This internal conflict makes Gillikinese characters particularly interesting to play, as they often struggle with privilege, education, and moral responsibility.</p>\n\n<h2>Racial Traits</h2>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Trait</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Ability Score Increase</strong></td>\n<td>Your Intelligence score increases by 1, and one other ability score of your choice increases by 1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Age</strong></td>\n<td>Gillikinese mature at the same rate as other humans and live less than a century.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Size</strong></td>\n<td>Medium. Gillikinese range from 5 to 6 feet tall.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Speed</strong></td>\n<td>30 feet</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Languages</strong></td>\n<td>Common (Ozian), plus one of your choice</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Gillikinese Education</h3>\n<p>You gain proficiency in one skill of your choice from: Arcana, History, Investigation, or Religion. Additionally, you can read, write, and speak one additional language of your choice.</p>\n\n<h3>Social Graces</h3>\n<p>You have advantage on Charisma (Persuasion) checks when interacting with Gillikinese nobility or academic institutions. You also have proficiency with one musical instrument or artisan's tools of your choice.</p>\n\n<h3>Purple Heritage</h3>\n<p>The purple landscapes of Gillikin have left their mark. You have advantage on saving throws against being charmed, representing the Gillikinese tradition of emotional restraint and intellectual control.</p>\n\n<h2>Culture</h2>\n\n<p>Gillikinese society is stratified by education and family lineage. The highest echelons are occupied by graduates of Shiz University and their descendants, while skilled craftspeople, merchants, and farmers make up the middle and lower classes. Social mobility is possible through education, but access to Shiz is often dependent on family connections and wealth.</p>\n\n<p>Purple is the signature color of Gillikin, appearing in everything from clothing to architecture. Wearing purple—particularly deep, rich shades—is a status symbol. The aristocracy tends toward violet and royal purple, while commoners wear lighter lavenders and mauves.</p>\n\n<p>Intellectual pursuits are highly valued. A Gillikinese who cannot engage in philosophical debate or lacks knowledge of history and the arts is considered uncultured, regardless of their wealth. Many Gillikinese homes contain extensive libraries, and literacy rates are higher in Gillikin than anywhere else in Oz.</p>\n\n<h2>Naming Conventions</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Male Names:</strong> Avaric, Crope, Tibbett, Boq, Frexspar</p>\n\n<p><strong>Female Names:</strong> Glinda, Pfannee, Shenshen, Milla, Thessaly</p>\n\n<p><strong>Family Names:</strong> Arduenna, Tigelaar, Upland, Tenmeadows</p>\n\n<p>Gillikinese often use initials or shortened versions of their names in casual settings, but full names are used in formal situations. Triple-barreled surnames are common among the aristocracy.</p>\n\n<h2>Roleplaying a Gillikinese</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Personality Traits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>I believe every problem can be solved through reason and education.</li>\n<li>I unconsciously judge others by their grammar and vocabulary.</li>\n<li>I collect books and can't resist visiting libraries wherever I go.</li>\n<li>I struggle to express emotion openly, preferring intellectual discussion.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Ideals:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Knowledge.</strong> Education is the path to enlightenment and progress. (Good)</li>\n<li><strong>Tradition.</strong> The old ways have endured for good reason. (Lawful)</li>\n<li><strong>Reform.</strong> The systems that built Gillikin's success are fundamentally unjust. (Chaotic)</li>\n<li><strong>Excellence.</strong> Mediocrity is unacceptable in any endeavor. (Any)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Bonds:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>My family's reputation is everything to me.</li>\n<li>I owe my education to a mentor who saw potential in me.</li>\n<li>I seek to restore my family's lost fortune/status.</li>\n<li>A book I read changed my life, and I seek its author.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Flaws:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>I assume I'm the smartest person in the room.</li>\n<li>I struggle to relate to those without formal education.</li>\n<li>I'm ashamed of my family's history with Animal exploitation.</li>\n<li>I value appearance and status more than I'd like to admit.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>GM Notes</h2>\n\n<p>Gillikinese characters work well as party intellectuals, diplomats, or reformed aristocrats grappling with privilege. Their educational background makes them natural scholars, wizards, or bards. Consider having them struggle with the gap between theoretical knowledge and practical reality.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Notable Gillikinese NPCs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Glinda Upland - The Good Witch, social climber turned leader</li>\n<li>Avaric Tenmeadows - Wealthy student, opportunist</li>\n<li>Crope and Tibbett - Scholars at Shiz, partners in research and life</li>\n<li>Madame Morrible - Headmistress of Shiz, dangerous manipulator</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Plot Hooks:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The party is hired to recover a rare book stolen from a Gillikinese library.</li>\n<li>A Gillikinese noble seeks redemption by aiding Animal refugees.</li>\n<li>Ancient secrets in the Shiz University archives hold the key to the campaign's mystery.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Related Entries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('exploration/regions/gillikin', 'Gillikin'); return false;\">Gillikin (Region)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('character/classes/the-adept', 'The Adept'); return false;\">The Adept</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('npcs/elphaba-thropp', 'Elphaba Thropp'); return false;\">Elphaba Thropp</a></li>\n</ul>",
