    "character/classes/the-adept": {
      "title": "The Adept",
      "content": "<h1>The Adept</h1>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>\"Magic isn't meant to be tamed. It's meant to be survived—and only if you're clever enough to read what was never meant to be read.\"</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h2>Overview</h2>\n\n<p>The Adept is one who has glimpsed the deeper magics of Oz—the forbidden knowledge inscribed in the Grimmerie, passed down through whispers of the Kumbric tradition, or channeled through ancient Quadling rites. Unlike the natural magic of witches or the faith-driven power of Unionists, the Adept's power comes from study, discipline, and often dangerous bargains with forces beyond mortal ken.</p>\n\n<p>To become an Adept is to walk a knife's edge between power and corruption. The Grimmerie itself is said to change those who read it, twisting their bodies and minds even as it grants them unimaginable abilities. Many Adepts hide their practice, knowing that the Emerald City's authorities—and the Unionist Church—would see them burned as witches.</p>\n\n<p>Some Adepts are scholars who stumbled onto forbidden texts. Others are desperate souls seeking power to right wrongs. Still others are driven by pure curiosity, willing to risk everything to understand the fundamental nature of Oz's magic.</p>\n\n<h2>Class Features</h2>\n\n<h3>Hit Points</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hit Dice:</strong> 1d6 per Adept level</li>\n<li><strong>Hit Points at 1st Level:</strong> 6 + your Constitution modifier</li>\n<li><strong>Hit Points at Higher Levels:</strong> 1d6 (or 4) + your Constitution modifier per Adept level after 1st</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Proficiencies</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Armor:</strong> None</li>\n<li><strong>Weapons:</strong> Daggers, darts, slings, quarterstaffs, light crossbows</li>\n<li><strong>Tools:</strong> None</li>\n<li><strong>Saving Throws:</strong> Intelligence, Wisdom</li>\n<li><strong>Skills:</strong> Choose two from Arcana, Deception, History, Insight, Investigation, Religion</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Equipment</h3>\n<p>You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>(a) a quarterstaff or (b) a dagger</li>\n<li>(a) a component pouch or (b) a Grimmerie page fragment (arcane focus)</li>\n<li>(a) a scholar's pack or (b) an explorer's pack</li>\n<li>A spellbook containing six 1st-level Adept spells</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>The Adept Table</h2>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Level</th>\n<th>Prof. Bonus</th>\n<th>Features</th>\n<th>Cantrips Known</th>\n<th>1st</th>\n<th>2nd</th>\n<th>3rd</th>\n<th>4th</th>\n<th>5th</th>\n<th>6th</th>\n<th>7th</th>\n<th>8th</th>\n<th>9th</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1st</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Spellcasting, Grimmerie Lore</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2nd</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Adept Tradition</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3rd</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Witch-Mark</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4th</td>\n<td>+2</td>\n<td>Ability Score Improvement</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5th</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6th</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>Tradition Feature</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7th</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8th</td>\n<td>+3</td>\n<td>Ability Score Improvement</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9th</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10th</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>Tradition Feature</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11th</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>12th</td>\n<td>+4</td>\n<td>Ability Score Improvement</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>13th</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14th</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n<td>Tradition Feature</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15th</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>16th</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n<td>Ability Score Improvement</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>17th</td>\n<td>+6</td>\n<td>-</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>18th</td>\n<td>+6</td>\n<td>Spell Mastery</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>19th</td>\n<td>+6</td>\n<td>Ability Score Improvement</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>20th</td>\n<td>+6</td>\n<td>Signature Spell</td>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Class Features (Detailed)</h2>\n\n<h3>Spellcasting (Level 1)</h3>\n<p>As a student of arcane magic, you have a spellbook containing spells drawn from the Grimmerie tradition and other forbidden sources.</p>\n\n<h3>Grimmerie Lore (Level 1)</h3>\n<p>You can read magical script that would be incomprehensible to others. You have advantage on Intelligence (Arcana) checks to identify spells, decipher magical writing, or understand the nature of magical effects. Additionally, you can cast <em>Detect Magic</em> as a ritual without having it prepared.</p>\n\n<h3>Witch-Mark (Level 3)</h3>\n<p>Extended exposure to forbidden magic has left its mark on you. Choose one physical manifestation: unusual eye color (green-tinged skin like Elphaba's is rare), hair that moves of its own accord, eyes that occasionally glow when casting, or fingers stained with magical ink. This mark gives you advantage on Intimidation checks against those who fear magic, but disadvantage on Persuasion checks with Unionists and witch-hunters.</p>\n\n<h3>Spell Mastery (Level 18)</h3>\n<p>You have achieved such mastery over certain spells that you can cast them at will. Choose one 1st-level Adept spell and one 2nd-level Adept spell. You can cast those spells at their lowest level without expending a spell slot.</p>\n\n<h3>Signature Spell (Level 20)</h3>\n<p>Choose one 3rd-level Adept spell as your signature spell. You can cast it once without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to do so when you finish a short or long rest.</p>\n\n<h2>Adept Traditions</h2>\n\n<p>At 2nd level, you choose a tradition that shapes your practice of magic.</p>\n\n<h3>The Reader</h3>\n\n<p>You have gained access to pages from the Grimmerie itself, or other texts of comparable power. Your magic is raw, dangerous, and incredibly potent.</p>\n\n<h4>Reader Features</h4>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Adept Level</th>\n<th>Feature</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>2nd</td>\n<td>Direct Reading, Grimmerie Fragment</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6th</td>\n<td>Empowered Casting</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10th</td>\n<td>Corruption Resistance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14th</td>\n<td>Reality Rewriting</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h5>Direct Reading (Level 2)</h5>\n<p>When you cast a spell of 1st level or higher, you can choose to read directly from the Grimmerie (or your fragment). The spell is cast at one level higher than the slot expended, but you take 1d6 necrotic damage per spell level. This damage cannot be reduced or prevented.</p>\n\n<h5>Empowered Casting (Level 6)</h5>\n<p>When you use Direct Reading, you can reroll any number of the spell's damage dice once.</p>\n\n<h5>Corruption Resistance (Level 10)</h5>\n<p>Your extended exposure to the Grimmerie has hardened you against its effects. You have resistance to necrotic damage, and you have advantage on saving throws against magical effects that would transform or corrupt you.</p>\n\n<h5>Reality Rewriting (Level 14)</h5>\n<p>Once per long rest, you can read from the deepest pages. When you cast a spell of 5th level or lower, you can change its target, range, or area of effect to something dramatically different, subject to DM approval. This always deals 5d6 necrotic damage to you.</p>\n\n<h3>The Domingon</h3>\n\n<p>You follow the Quadling tradition of trance magic, communicating with spirits and drawing power from the deep places of Oz.</p>\n\n<h4>Domingon Features</h4>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Adept Level</th>\n<th>Feature</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>2nd</td>\n<td>Trance State, Spirit Speech</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6th</td>\n<td>Deep Trance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10th</td>\n<td>Spirit Guardian</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14th</td>\n<td>Prophetic Vision</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h5>Trance State (Level 2)</h5>\n<p>You can enter a meditative trance as a bonus action. While in this state, you have advantage on Wisdom saving throws and can sense the presence of spirits within 60 feet. You can maintain this trance for up to 10 minutes, and can use it a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum 1) per long rest.</p>\n\n<h5>Deep Trance (Level 6)</h5>\n<p>While in your Trance State, you can cast <em>Speak with Dead</em> without expending a spell slot once per long rest.</p>\n\n<h5>Spirit Guardian (Level 10)</h5>\n<p>You have formed a bond with a spirit of the Quadling marshes. Once per long rest, you can summon this spirit to protect you. For 1 minute, the spirit grants you +2 to AC and you have advantage on death saving throws.</p>\n\n<h5>Prophetic Vision (Level 14)</h5>\n<p>Once per long rest, you can enter a prophetic trance. For 10 minutes, you experience visions of possible futures. The DM provides you with three glimpses of events that might occur in the next 24 hours, though which (if any) come to pass depends on the choices made.</p>\n\n<h2>Multiclassing</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Intelligence 13</p>\n<p><strong>Proficiencies Gained:</strong> Light armor, one skill from the Adept skill list</p>\n\n<h2>GM Notes</h2>\n\n<p>The Adept class represents the dangerous pursuit of arcane knowledge in Oz. Unlike traditional wizards, Adepts are drawing on sources of magic that actively corrupt and change them. Consider the physical and psychological toll of their power.</p>\n\n<p>The Reader tradition is high-risk, high-reward, perfect for characters willing to sacrifice themselves for power. The Domingon tradition offers a more sustainable but still dangerous path, connecting to Oz's spiritual traditions.</p>\n\n<p>Notable Adepts in Oz lore include Elphaba (Reader), Madame Morrible (Reader), and Candle (Domingon).</p>\n\n<h2>Related Entries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('magic/spells/grimmerie/memory-jar', 'Memory Jar'); return false;\">Memory Jar (Spell)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('npcs/elphaba-thropp', 'Elphaba Thropp'); return false;\">Elphaba Thropp</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('objects/magic-items/legendary/the-grimmerie', 'The Grimmerie'); return false;\">The Grimmerie</a></li>\n</ul>",
