    "exploration/regions/gillikin": {
      "title": "Gillikin",
      "content": "<h1>Gillikin</h1>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>\"In Gillikin, knowledge is currency, purple is power, and everyone is three bad investments away from becoming very interested in revolutionary politics.\"</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h2>Overview</h2>\n\n<p>Gillikin is the northern province of Oz, a land of deep forests, rolling purple hills, and ancient traditions. It is home to Shiz University, the greatest center of learning in all of Oz, and to the old aristocracy who have shaped Oz's culture for centuries. Purple dominates the landscape—from the violet-tinged forests to the amethyst stone of noble estates.</p>\n\n<h2>Geography</h2>\n\n<h3>Terrain</h3>\n<p>Gillikin is characterized by dense deciduous forests that take on purple hues in certain light, particularly at dawn and dusk. The terrain is hilly and crisscrossed by clear streams that feed into larger rivers. The soil is rich and dark, supporting both agriculture and the famous purple-blooming flowers that give the region its signature color.</p>\n\n<p>The climate is temperate with distinct seasons. Winters can be harsh, particularly in the northern reaches near the Pertha Hills, while summers are mild and pleasant. Autumn is spectacular, as the forests turn brilliant shades of purple, crimson, and gold.</p>\n\n<h3>Borders</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>North:</strong> The Deadly Desert</li>\n<li><strong>East:</strong> The Emerald City and the border with Munchkinland</li>\n<li><strong>South:</strong> The Emerald City</li>\n<li><strong>West:</strong> The Vinkus, separated by rough terrain</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Major Locations</h2>\n\n<h3>Shiz University</h3>\n<p><em>See full entry: <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('exploration/locations/shiz-university', 'Shiz University'); return false;\">Shiz University</a></em></p>\n<p>The heart of Gillikin intellectual life, Shiz is where the brightest minds of Oz gather—and where dangerous ideas are born. It was here that Elphaba Thropp and Galinda (later Glinda) studied, and where Dr. Dillamond taught before his murder.</p>\n\n<h3>The Pertha Hills</h3>\n<p>A remote, mountainous region in northern Gillikin, the Pertha Hills are home to isolated communities and, rumor has it, practicing witches who hide from persecution. The landscape is wild and beautiful, with few roads and fewer visitors. Yackle's estate was located somewhere in these hills.</p>\n\n<h3>Tenmeadows</h3>\n<p>An estate belonging to the wealthy Tenmeadows family, representing old Gillikin money. The grounds are extensive and carefully manicured, a display of aristocratic power and taste.</p>\n\n<h3>St. Glinda's Mauntery</h3>\n<p>One of the most prestigious maunteries in Oz, St. Glinda's (ironically named before Glinda became famous) houses an order of scholarly maunts who maintain an impressive library. Some sisters secretly sympathize with the Animal resistance.</p>\n\n<h3>Crage Hall</h3>\n<p>The women's college at Shiz University, Crage Hall has produced many of Oz's most influential women—for better or worse. Glinda and Elphaba both resided here during their university days.</p>\n\n<h2>Inhabitants</h2>\n\n<h3>Demographics</h3>\n<p>Gillikin has a population of approximately 200,000, concentrated in Shiz and the surrounding towns. The population is primarily human, with a small but historically significant Animal minority that has been decimated by persecution.</p>\n\n<p>The society is heavily stratified by education and class. The upper class consists of university-educated aristocrats and wealthy merchant families. The middle class includes skilled artisans, lower-level academics, and successful farmers. The lower class works the land, serves in noble households, or labors in shops and mills.</p>\n\n<h3>Notable Figures</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('npcs/elphaba-thropp', 'Elphaba Thropp'); return false;\">Elphaba Thropp</a> - The Wicked Witch of the West, Shiz alumna</li>\n<li>Glinda Upland - The Good Witch, Gillikin aristocrat</li>\n<li>Madame Morrible - Former Headmistress of Crage Hall</li>\n<li>Avaric Tenmeadows - Wealthy student and opportunist</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Animals in Gillikin</h3>\n<p>Gillikin once had a thriving Animal population, particularly in academic circles. Dr. Dillamond, the Goat professor at Shiz, was the most famous. Since the rise of Animal persecution, many have fled or been Silenced. Those who remain live in hiding or have abandoned their claims to personhood.</p>\n\n<h2>Culture</h2>\n\n<h3>Society</h3>\n<p>Gillikinese culture revolves around education, refinement, and the careful maintenance of social hierarchies. Conversation is an art form, and the ability to quote philosophers or debate theology is highly valued. Dinner parties can make or break social standing.</p>\n\n<p>Purple is omnipresent—in clothing, decoration, and architecture. The shade of purple one wears communicates social standing, with deeper, richer purples reserved for the aristocracy. To appear in public wearing inappropriate purple is a serious faux pas.</p>\n\n<p>There is a deep strain of hypocrisy in Gillikinese culture. The same people who debate ethics and morality in academic halls will turn a blind eye to the persecution of Animals or the suffering of the poor. This cognitive dissonance is carefully maintained through elaborate social rituals and willful ignorance.</p>\n\n<h3>Religion</h3>\n<p>Gillikin is the intellectual heart of Unionism, home to many of the faith's greatest theological scholars. The debate between orthodox and reform Unionism is particularly intense here, with university professors and church officials engaging in sometimes bitter disputes.</p>\n\n<p>There are also remnants of Lurline worship in the countryside, practiced quietly by those who remember the old ways. The Pertha Hills are rumored to harbor Pleasure Faith practitioners.</p>\n\n<h3>Economy</h3>\n<p>Gillikin's economy is based on education, skilled crafts, and agriculture. Shiz University is the largest employer and economic driver, bringing students and money from across Oz. The region is known for fine textiles, particularly purple-dyed fabrics, as well as books, furniture, and other products requiring skilled craftsmanship.</p>\n\n<p>Agriculture focuses on grain, orchards, and the cultivation of purple-blooming flowers used for dyes. Large estates operate as self-sufficient economic units, while smaller farms struggle under debt to aristocratic landowners.</p>\n\n<h2>History</h2>\n\n<p>Gillikin has always been Oz's intellectual center. When Lurline departed and Ozma took the throne, the region's scholars became the keepers of knowledge and tradition. Over centuries, this evolved into a hereditary aristocracy based on education and refinement.</p>\n\n<p>Shiz University was founded over five hundred years ago, originally as a monastery devoted to the study of Lurline's teachings. As Unionism rose, the university secularized but maintained its prestige. It became the training ground for Oz's ruling class.</p>\n\n<p>During the Wizard's reign, Gillikin largely cooperated with the new government, seeing opportunity in the changing power structure. Many Gillikinese aristocrats secured positions in the Wizard's administration. This collaboration continued under Emperor Shell, though some Gillikinese intellectuals have begun to quietly question the government's increasingly authoritarian policies.</p>\n\n<p>The persecution of Animals hit Gillikin particularly hard, as many Animals held positions at Shiz and in Gillikinese society. Dr. Dillamond's murder marked a turning point, radicalizing some students (like Elphaba) while others retreated into comfortable denial.</p>\n\n<h2>Current Situation</h2>\n\n<p>Gillikin is a region in tension. The old aristocracy clings to power and privilege, but economic pressures and political changes threaten their position. The Munchkinland secession has disrupted trade and raised uncomfortable questions about Oz's unity. Some Gillikinese intellectuals quietly support reform or even revolution, while others double down on tradition.</p>\n\n<p>The persecution of Animals continues, though some Gillikinese shelter Animal refugees at great personal risk. The question of what Shiz knew and when it knew it about the government's plans haunts the university community.</p>\n\n<p>Emperor Shell's regime views Gillikin with suspicion—too educated, too prone to asking questions. There have been quiet purges of university faculty, always with plausible official explanations. Fear is growing beneath the polished surface of Gillikinese society.</p>\n\n<h2>Hazards</h2>\n\n<h3>Environmental</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Dense forests where travelers can easily become lost</li>\n<li>Harsh winters in the northern regions</li>\n<li>Wild animals (non-sentient) in remote areas</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Political</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Social ostracism for violating class conventions</li>\n<li>Secret police monitoring university radicals</li>\n<li>Informants in academic and social circles</li>\n<li>Witch-hunters seeking forbidden magic users</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Creatures</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Bears (possibly Animals) in the forests</li>\n<li>Wolves in remote areas</li>\n<li>Grimmerie manifestations near places of power</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Random Encounters</h2>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>d12</th>\n<th>Encounter</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>A Gillikinese noble traveling with guards, suspicious of strangers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>University students debating philosophy, happy to include travelers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>A maunt traveling alone, may offer sanctuary or information</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4-5</td>\n<td>Gale Force patrol checking papers and searching for Animal refugees</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>Merchants transporting purple dyes and fine fabrics</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>A wandering bear who may or may not be an Animal in hiding</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>A wealthy family's carriage broken down, needing assistance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9</td>\n<td>A witch-hunter questioning locals about magical activity</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>Farmers bringing goods to market, willing to trade or gossip</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11</td>\n<td>An Animal refugee hiding in the woods, desperate for help</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>12</td>\n<td>Strange lights in the forest—magic, or something else?</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Adventure Hooks</h2>\n\n<ol>\n<li>A professor at Shiz has disappeared after discovering something in the restricted archives. The party is hired to investigate.</li>\n<li>An Animal noble family seeks help smuggling their children to safety before the Gale Force comes for them.</li>\n<li>A Gillikinese aristocrat believes they are being haunted by the ghost of an Animal their family wronged. Are they right?</li>\n<li>The party discovers evidence that a respected maunt is secretly practicing Grimmerie magic. What do they do with this knowledge?</li>\n<li>A valuable book containing dangerous magical knowledge has been stolen from Shiz University. Multiple factions want it, and the party is caught in the middle.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>GM Notes</h2>\n\n<p>Gillikin is perfect for campaigns focused on intrigue, moral complexity, and the tension between tradition and change. The region's emphasis on education and culture creates interesting roleplay opportunities, while the underlying injustice and collaboration with authoritarianism provide compelling conflicts.</p>\n\n<p>Use Gillikin to explore themes of privilege, complicity, and the responsibility of the educated. Characters may find themselves torn between the comfort of Gillikinese society and the moral imperative to resist injustice.</p>\n\n<p>The purple aesthetic can be visually striking in descriptions. Play up the contrast between the beautiful, refined surface of Gillikinese culture and the ugly realities it conceals.</p>\n\n<h2>Related Entries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('character/races/humans/gillikinese', 'Gillikinese'); return false;\">Gillikinese (Race)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('exploration/locations/shiz-university', 'Shiz University'); return false;\">Shiz University</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('npcs/elphaba-thropp', 'Elphaba Thropp'); return false;\">Elphaba Thropp</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('exploration/regions/emerald-city', 'The Emerald City'); return false;\">The Emerald City</a></li>\n</ul>",
      "related": [
        "character/races/humans/gillikinese",
        "exploration/locations/shiz-university",
        "npcs/elphaba-thropp",
