    "magic/spells/grimmerie/memory-jar": {
      "title": "Memory Jar",
      "content": "<h1>Memory Jar</h1>\n\n<p><em>2nd-level enchantment (Grimmerie)</em></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>\"She kept her grief in a jar on the shelf, next to the dried lavender and the mouse bones. Some days she took it down and let herself remember. Most days, she was grateful to forget.\"</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h2>Spell Details</h2>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Property</th>\n<th>Value</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Level</strong></td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>School</strong></td>\n<td>Enchantment</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Casting Time</strong></td>\n<td>1 minute</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Range</strong></td>\n<td>Touch</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Components</strong></td>\n<td>V, S, M (a glass jar worth at least 10 gp)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Duration</strong></td>\n<td>Until dispelled</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Tradition</strong></td>\n<td>Grimmerie, Witch (Hedge)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Description</h2>\n\n<p>You touch a willing creature and extract a specific memory, storing it in a glass jar. The creature must concentrate on the memory they wish to remove while you cast this spell. The memory can be as short as a single moment or as long as one hour of continuous experience.</p>\n\n<p>Once the memory is extracted and stored in the jar, the creature no longer has any recollection of the events contained in that memory. The jar glows faintly with a color corresponding to the emotional content of the memory: warm gold for joy, deep blue for sadness, red for anger, green for envy, and so forth.</p>\n\n<p>A creature can restore a memory by opening the jar and breathing in its contents (an action). The memory returns instantly and completely. Once restored, the jar becomes empty and nonmagical.</p>\n\n<p>If the jar is broken while containing a memory, the memory is lost forever and cannot be recovered by any means short of a <em>Wish</em> spell. The creature who lost the memory will never recall it, though they may be aware that something is missing.</p>\n\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, you can extract and store an additional hour of memories for each slot level above 2nd. These can be from the same creature or different willing creatures, but each memory requires its own jar.</p>\n\n<h2>Spell Lists</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Adept</li>\n<li>Witch</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Lore</h2>\n\n<p>The Memory Jar spell is ancient, predating even the Grimmerie's creation. Some scholars believe it originated with the Kumbric Witch, who is said to have stored millennia of memories in jars hidden throughout Oz. Others claim it was developed by grieving Quadling domingons who sought to ease the pain of loss.</p>\n\n<p>During the Wizard's reign, Memory Jar became a tool of oppression. Political prisoners were forced to surrender memories of resistance activities. Some were made to forget their own identities. The practice became so notorious that possession of a memory jar is now illegal in the Emerald City, punishable by imprisonment.</p>\n\n<p>Yet the spell persists, used by those seeking to escape trauma, hide dangerous knowledge, or preserve precious moments. In the underground market, memory jars sell for enormous sums—particularly those containing the final moments of famous individuals or lost magical knowledge.</p>\n\n<p>There are disturbing rumors of collectors who steal others' memories, building vast libraries of experiences they can browse like books. Such individuals are hunted by both the authorities and those they've victimized.</p>\n\n<h2>GM Notes</h2>\n\n<p>Memory Jar is a spell with profound narrative implications. Use it sparingly and thoughtfully. A character who removes a traumatic memory doesn't heal from it—they simply no longer know it exists. This can lead to dangerous situations where they repeat past mistakes.</p>\n\n<p>Consider the ethical questions: Is it right to remove a memory, even a painful one? What if that memory is crucial to someone's identity? What happens when a character discovers they've had memories removed without their knowledge?</p>\n\n<p>Memory jars make excellent quest objects. The party might need to recover a stolen memory jar, protect someone's hidden memories, or decide whether to restore a memory that might destroy someone they care about.</p>\n\n<p>The spell can also be used for information storage. An Adept might extract their knowledge of a powerful spell and hide it away, ensuring it doesn't die with them but also can't be tortured out of them.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Creative Uses:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Removing knowledge of a secret location before being captured</li>\n<li>Storing happy memories to revisit during dark times</li>\n<li>Hiding evidence of a crime</li>\n<li>Creating a false alibi (\"I don't remember where I was that night\")</li>\n<li>Preserving the memories of the dying</li>\n<li>Trading memories as currency in certain underground markets</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Limitations and Considerations:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The spell requires a willing subject—forcing someone to forget is a different, darker magic</li>\n<li>Breaking a memory jar is permanent destruction</li>\n<li>Some memories are too large or too fundamental to identity to be removed</li>\n<li>Removing a memory doesn't remove skills or knowledge gained from it, leading to strange gaps in understanding</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Related Entries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('character/classes/the-adept', 'The Adept'); return false;\">The Adept</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('objects/magic-items/uncommon/memory-jar-filled', 'Memory Jar (Filled)'); return false;\">Memory Jar (Magic Item)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('conditions/oz-specific/memory-rot', 'Memory Rot'); return false;\">Memory Rot (Condition)</a></li>\n</ul>",
      "related": [
        "character/classes/the-adept",
        "objects/magic-items/uncommon/memory-jar-filled",
        "conditions/oz-specific/memory-rot"
      ],
      "tags": ["spell", "grimmerie", "enchantment", "memory", "template"],
