    "character/backgrounds/shiz-dropout": {
      "title": "Shiz Dropout",
      "content": "<h1>Shiz Dropout</h1>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>\"I left before they could expel me. Better to walk away than be thrown out, my father always said. He stopped saying much of anything to me after that.\"</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h2>Description</h2>\n\n<p>You were a student at Shiz University, the most prestigious institution of learning in all of Oz. Whether you studied for a single semester or made it nearly to graduation, something happened that ended your academic career. Perhaps you were expelled for unauthorized magical experimentation, or you discovered a truth too dangerous to ignore. Maybe you simply couldn't afford the tuition, or the politics of academic life proved too much to stomach. Whatever the reason, you left Shiz before earning your degree.</p>\n\n<p>This background carries both privilege and shame. You received enough education to set you apart from common folk, learning skills and making connections that will serve you for life. But you also bear the stigma of failure in Gillikinese society, where a Shiz education is the key to advancement. Your family may have been disappointed or furious. Your former friends may have abandoned you. Yet you've also seen behind the curtain of Oz's intellectual elite, and you know that their refinement often masks corruption and cowardice.</p>\n\n<p>Many Shiz dropouts become adventurers, using the skills they learned to make their way in a world that has closed its doors to them. Some seek to prove they were right to leave. Others hunt for redemption, hoping to finish what they started or right the wrongs that drove them away.</p>\n\n<h2>Skill Proficiencies</h2>\n\n<p>Choose two from: Arcana, History, Investigation, Persuasion</p>\n\n<h2>Tool Proficiencies</h2>\n\n<p>Choose one type of artisan's tools or one musical instrument</p>\n\n<h2>Languages</h2>\n\n<p>One of your choice (academic study)</p>\n\n<h2>Equipment</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A set of fine clothes (purple-trimmed, slightly worn)</li>\n<li>A Shiz University scarf or pin (you couldn't quite bring yourself to throw it away)</li>\n<li>A letter from someone you left behind (friend, rival, or lover)</li>\n<li>One academic book from your studies</li>\n<li>A belt pouch containing 15 gp</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Feature: Academic Network</h2>\n\n<p>Despite leaving Shiz, you still have connections in academic circles throughout Oz. When you're in a settlement with a library, university, or scholarly institution, you can gain access to academic resources and seek out learned individuals who might help you—for old times' sake, shared intellectual interests, or in exchange for interesting information.</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, you can usually identify fellow Shiz students or alumni on sight, recognizing the subtle markers of Shiz culture (speech patterns, fashion choices, mannerisms). Whether they'll be friendly or hostile depends on the circumstances and how you left, but at least you'll know you're dealing with someone from your world.</p>\n\n<h2>Suggested Characteristics</h2>\n\n<p>Shiz dropouts are shaped by their incomplete education and the circumstances of their departure. Some are bitter about what they lost. Others are relieved to be free of academic constraints. All carry the weight of unfinished business.</p>\n\n<h3>Personality Traits</h3>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>d8</th>\n<th>Personality Trait</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>I correct people's grammar and pronunciation without thinking.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>I'm more comfortable with books than people.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>I name-drop my time at Shiz constantly, even though I didn't finish.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>I'm suspicious of authority figures, especially academic ones.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>I have a chip on my shoulder about not having a degree.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>I collect knowledge obsessively, trying to fill the gaps in my education.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>I'm surprisingly practical for someone with a Shiz background.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>I hide my Shiz past, ashamed of both the privilege and the failure.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Ideals</h3>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>d6</th>\n<th>Ideal</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td><strong>Knowledge.</strong> Truth matters more than degrees or social standing. (Good)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td><strong>Rebellion.</strong> The academic establishment is corrupt and must be challenged. (Chaotic)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td><strong>Redemption.</strong> I will prove I was worthy of Shiz all along. (Lawful)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td><strong>Independence.</strong> I don't need their approval to be successful. (Chaotic)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td><strong>Justice.</strong> I left because I saw injustice and refused to be complicit. (Good)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td><strong>Ambition.</strong> I'll show them all what I'm capable of. (Evil)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Bonds</h3>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>d6</th>\n<th>Bond</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>I left someone I loved behind at Shiz, and I think about them every day.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>A professor helped me when I needed it most. I owe them everything.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>I took something from Shiz when I left—a book, an artifact, or knowledge I wasn't supposed to have.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>My family sacrificed everything to send me to Shiz. I need to make it worth it somehow.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>I witnessed something terrible at Shiz that no one believed. I need to expose the truth.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>I have a rival from my Shiz days who I both hate and miss.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Flaws</h3>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>d6</th>\n<th>Flaw</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>I'm convinced I'm smarter than everyone else, despite my incomplete education.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>I drink too much when I think about what I gave up.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>I'm terrified of being exposed as a fraud or failure.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>I can't resist showing off my knowledge, even when it's dangerous.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>I'm obsessed with returning to Shiz, even though it would be a disaster.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>I judge people harshly based on their education and accent.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Customization</h2>\n\n<p>Consider the specifics of your time at Shiz:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>What did you study?</strong> Sorcery, Life Sciences, History, Theology, or something else?</li>\n<li><strong>Why did you leave?</strong> Expelled, financial problems, moral crisis, personal tragedy, or something else?</li>\n<li><strong>When did you leave?</strong> First year, midway through, or just before graduation?</li>\n<li><strong>Who did you know?</strong> Did you overlap with any famous Shiz students like Elphaba or Glinda?</li>\n<li><strong>What did you take with you?</strong> Knowledge, objects, or secrets?</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Related Entries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('exploration/locations/shiz-university', 'Shiz University'); return false;\">Shiz University</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('exploration/regions/gillikin', 'Gillikin'); return false;\">Gillikin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('character/races/humans/gillikinese', 'Gillikinese'); return false;\">Gillikinese (Race)</a></li>\n</ul>",
