    "objects/magic-items/uncommon/silver-slippers": {
      "title": "Silver Slippers",
      "content": "<h1>Silver Slippers</h1>\n\n<p><em>Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>\"Three clicks of the heels, they say, and you're home. But what if you don't know where home is anymore?\"</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h2>Description</h2>\n\n<p>These elegant slippers are crafted from hammered silver that somehow remains flexible and comfortable despite its metallic nature. They fit any foot that attempts to wear them, reshaping themselves instantly to provide perfect comfort. The silver has a soft sheen that catches the light, and tiny runes are etched along the straps in a language that predates modern Ozian script.</p>\n\n<p>The slippers weigh almost nothing and make no sound when walking, despite being made of metal. They never tarnish or scratch, maintaining their pristine appearance no matter how hard they're worn. When not being worn, they fold flat and can easily be tucked into a pocket or pack.</p>\n\n<h2>History</h2>\n\n<p>The Silver Slippers are one of several pairs of magical shoes known to exist in Oz, though perhaps not as famous as the Ruby Slippers that once belonged to Nessarose Thropp, the Wicked Witch of the East. The origins of these silver shoes are mysterious—some claim they were crafted by the Gnome King of Ev, while others believe they're a creation of Lurline herself, gifts left behind when she departed Oz.</p>\n\n<p>The slippers have passed through many hands over the centuries. They were once owned by a wealthy Gillikinese merchant who used them to build a trading empire, appearing in distant markets overnight. A Quadling resistance leader wore them during the genocide, saving dozens of refugees by transporting them to safety. Most recently, they were held in the private collection of a noble family until they were stolen—or perhaps rescued—by person or persons unknown.</p>\n\n<h2>Properties</h2>\n\n<h3>Swift Travel</h3>\n<p>While wearing these slippers, your walking speed increases by 10 feet. Additionally, you ignore difficult terrain when walking.</p>\n\n<h3>Seven-League Stride</h3>\n<p>Once per long rest, you can activate the slippers' power by clicking your heels together three times and concentrating on a location you can visualize. You must have been to this location before, or have seen it clearly in a crystal ball, scrying pool, or similar divination. When you activate this power, you teleport to that location, appearing in the nearest unoccupied space if your intended destination is blocked.</p>\n\n<p>The teleportation can cross any distance within Oz, but it cannot cross the Deadly Desert or travel to other planes of existence. If you attempt to teleport somewhere you cannot reach, the magic fails but is not expended.</p>\n\n<h3>Always Steady</h3>\n<p>You have advantage on saving throws and ability checks made to avoid being knocked prone or moved against your will. Your feet find purchase where others would slip and fall.</p>\n\n<h2>Attunement</h2>\n\n<p>To attune to the Silver Slippers, you must wear them for one hour while walking a path that matters to you—toward something you seek or away from something you flee. During this time, you must think about where you truly belong in the world. The slippers will attune to you if they judge you worthy, though their criteria for worthiness remain mysterious.</p>\n\n<p>Once attuned, only you can wear the slippers. They will not fit anyone else until your attunement ends.</p>\n\n<h2>Lore & Legends</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Common Knowledge:</strong> Most people in Oz have heard stories of magical shoes that can transport their wearer great distances. The tales often involve someone desperately wishing to go home and finding themselves there with three clicks of their heels.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Rumors:</strong> Some claim that the Silver Slippers can cross the Deadly Desert, though this has never been proven. Others whisper that wearing them draws the attention of powerful beings who covet such items. There's a persistent story that the slippers will eventually take their wearer somewhere they don't expect—home, but not the home they imagined.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Misconceptions:</strong> Many believe the slippers will take you anywhere you want to go with a simple wish. In truth, the magic is more limited and requires genuine knowledge of your destination. Some think the slippers are indestructible, but they can be damaged or destroyed like any magical item—it's simply very difficult.</p>\n\n<p><strong>True Secrets:</strong> The Silver Slippers were created by Lurline as a fail-safe, intended to allow her chosen champions to retreat from danger or reach places of power quickly. They respond not just to where you want to go, but to where you need to be. On rare occasions, the slippers have taken their wearers somewhere other than their intended destination, always to a place where they were desperately needed—or where they needed to be for their own growth.</p>\n\n<p>The slippers also have a defensive property that few discover: if someone attempts to forcibly remove them from an attuned wearer, the slippers teleport both the wearer and themselves to a place the wearer thinks of as safe.</p>\n\n<h2>GM Notes</h2>\n\n<p>The Silver Slippers are powerful but not game-breaking. The once-per-long-rest teleportation is significant but limited, making it a strategic resource rather than a constant escape hatch. Use the slippers to enable dramatic moments—rescues, last-second escapes, or surprise appearances.</p>\n\n<p>Consider having the slippers' teleportation be imperfect in interesting ways. Perhaps the wearer arrives at their destination exhausted, or the magic attracts attention. Maybe crossing certain magical boundaries (like the wards around Kiamo Ko or the Emerald City) requires a saving throw or causes complications.</p>\n\n<p>The slippers work well as a quest reward or a contested object. Multiple factions might want them, leading to interesting choices for the party. Do they keep them, sell them, give them to someone in need, or destroy them to keep them out of dangerous hands?</p>\n\n<p><strong>Alternative Versions:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Silver Slippers (Rare):</strong> Can teleport twice per long rest and grant a +1 bonus to AC</li>\n<li><strong>Tarnished Silver Slippers (Common):</strong> Only grant the Swift Travel property, no teleportation</li>\n<li><strong>Silver Dancing Shoes (Uncommon):</strong> Focus on movement in combat, granting extra movement and the ability to disengage as a bonus action</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Related Entries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('objects/magic-items/legendary/ruby-slippers', 'Ruby Slippers'); return false;\">Ruby Slippers</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('npcs/nessarose-thropp', 'Nessarose Thropp'); return false;\">Nessarose Thropp</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"Tabs.openTab('objects/magic-items/rare/emerald-city-shoes', 'Emerald City Shoes'); return false;\">Emerald City Shoes</a></li>\n</ul>",
      "related": [
        "objects/magic-items/legendary/ruby-slippers",
        "npcs/nessarose-thropp",
        "objects/magic-items/rare/emerald-city-shoes"
      ],
